data.name: Machoke

attacks.name: Pummel
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 70 more damage.

data.flavorText: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

data.name: Machoke

attacks.name: Karate Chop
attacks.text: Does 50 damage minus 10 damage for each damage counter on Machoke.

attacks.name: Submission
attacks.text: Machoke does 20 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: Its muscular body is so powerful that it must wear a power-save belt to help regulate its motions.

abilities.name: Paranoid
abilities.text: As long as Machoke is Confused, Machoke's attacks do 50 more damage to the Defending Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Split Kick
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to each Defending Pokémon.

data.name: Machoke

attacks.name: Knuckle Down
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It always goes at its full power, but this very tough and durable Pokémon never gets tired.

attacks.name: Risky Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does no damage to the Defending Pokémon and Giovanni's Machoke does 100 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Headlock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, this attack does 20 damage.

attacks.name: Steady Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

data.name: Dark Machoke

attacks.name: Drag Off
attacks.text: Before doing damage, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with the Defending Pokémon. Do the damage to the new Defending Pokémon. This attack can't be used if your opponent has no Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Knock Back
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: While normally peaceful and friendly, the number of incidents involving cruel Machokes is rising.

data.name: Machoke

attacks.name: Last-Chance Chop
attacks.text: If this Pokémon's remaining HP is 10, this attack does 70 more damage.

data.flavorText: It happily carries heavy cargo to toughen up. It willingly does hard work for people.

abilities.name: Strikes Back
abilities.text: If Machoke is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Machoke is Knocked Out), put 1 damage counter on the Attacking Pokémon.

data.name: Machoke

attacks.name: Steady Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

attacks.name: Brick Break
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Machoke's boundless power is very dangerous, so it wears a belt that suppresses its energy.

data.name: Light Machoke

attacks.name: Return Home
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokémon, shuffle 1 of them and all cards attached to it into your deck.

attacks.name: Gentle Kick
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has no damage counters on it, this attack does 40 damage. If it has any, this attack does 20 damage.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon never gets tired, no matter what it does or how hard it works.
